properties.name: gritstone100
properties.desc: A 100 mile route around some of the best gritstone tors, outcrops, and edges in the High Peak - https://gritstone100.co.uk/

properties.name: Start
properties.desc: From Smithy Bridge head around the bowling green, cricket pitch, and towards the Village Hall

properties.name: Woodfall Lane
properties.desc: Turn left onto Woodfall Lane

properties.name: Post Office
properties.desc: Follow the track passed the tennis courts and into the woods. The PO has a great shop, caf, etc - lovely cakes :)

properties.name: Bridge
properties.desc: Go right across and up the steps

properties.name: Steps
properties.desc: Follow the clear track up hill

properties.name: Smallfield Lane
properties.desc: Cross the road, up the small stone steps and through the iron gate

properties.name: Church Gate
properties.desc: Go out and back in the first gate to enter the church yard and pass in front of the building

properties.name: St Nicholas' Church
properties.desc: Turn right at the end of the Bell Tower on the clear path.

properties.name: Graveyard
properties.desc: Turn left on the path that leads East through the graveyard.

properties.name: Gate
properties.desc: Go through the gate and carry on the path

properties.name: Bailey Hill
properties.desc: Exit the grave yard and go right, down hill, at Bailey Hill, so that the steep edge is directly on your left.

properties.name: Turn
properties.desc: Take the 90 degree left down the hill

properties.name: Rocher End Brook
properties.desc: Cross the brook and take  the path up into the field directly in front

properties.name: Broken Wall
properties.desc: Cross the wall and carry on up hill. Various lines here

properties.name: Bowsen
properties.desc: Bear right at the stone bar onto the clear track behind

properties.name: Stone Bench
properties.desc: Turn right at the stone bench and go up the hill on the clear track way

properties.name: Rocher Wood
properties.desc: Turn almost 180 left to go on the path along the edge

properties.name: Bench
properties.desc: Turn left before the bench  down the hill

properties.name: Rocher Head
properties.desc: Turn right on the clear track way

properties.name: Smallfield Lane 2
properties.desc: Cross the road and go over the stile opposite

properties.name: Bar Dike
properties.desc: Turn left towards Mortimer Road

properties.name: Mortimer Road
properties.desc: Cross the road and go through the gate on the clear "Dukes Road" on Broomhead Moor

properties.name: Hurrkling Edge
properties.desc: Great shelter among the stones about 50m to the left  of the path

properties.name: Last wall
properties.desc: Pass the high fell wall on the left

properties.name: Rushy Dike
properties.desc: Can be a ford at certain times of year

properties.name: Cartledge Brook
properties.desc: Take the much fainter path off the right, following the Northern bank of the brook

properties.name: Ford
properties.desc: Cross the brook and go up the clough along the line of grouse butts in a South-westerly direction

properties.name: Picnic tables (!?)
properties.desc: Just before the tables take the path on the left out of the clough onto Robin Hood Moss then follow the line of butts

properties.name: Wet Stones
properties.desc: At the last stones bear right of the well built butts to meet Howden Edge

properties.name: Howden Edge
properties.desc: Go right on the clear path heading North

properties.name: High Stones
properties.desc: The small cairn to the right is the highest point in South Yorkshire

properties.name: Wilfrey Neild
properties.desc: Natural gritstone window om Wilfrey Edge

properties.name: Wilfrey Edge
properties.desc: Turn right and take one of the fainter paths out towards the visible Margery Stones

properties.name: Trig Point
properties.desc:
Margery Hill.

Believed to have been part of a Bronze Age burial mound.

properties.name: Cut Gate End
properties.desc: Cross the much clearer cut gate and carry on

properties.name: Trig Point
properties.desc: Either carry strait on to Outer Edge...or take the hard left to Crow Stones and loop back

properties.name: Fords
properties.desc: Multiple small fords here. Path disappears. The line is always to the highest ground

properties.name: Hoar Stones
properties.desc: Pass the distinctive three Hoar Stones about 100m on your left

properties.name: Featherbed Moss
properties.desc: Turn left and head south towards the source of the River Derwent in the valley below

properties.name: Hoar Clough Head
properties.desc: Bear left on the last clough towards Shepheards Meeting Stones

properties.name: Shepheards Meeting Stones
properties.desc: Cross Hoar Clough (scramble) and take the path directly south, down hill, on the far bank. Excellent natural shelter

properties.name: River Derwent 1
properties.desc: Turn left at the river and follow it down stream on its Northern bank

properties.name: Coldwell Clough
properties.desc: Cross the clough and look for a safe place to cross the Derwent

properties.name: Sheep Fold
properties.desc: At the sheep fold climb the steep bank, the path can be totally lost here

properties.name: Fair Banks
properties.desc: Track the path south that follows the edge of the small plateau you are on

properties.name: Round Hill
properties.desc: Turn right and go up Round Hill

properties.name: Round Hill top
properties.desc: At the top of the hill take the clear path out towards Barrow Stones

properties.name: Gate
properties.desc: Pass through the gate and take the line left along the moor top. Strange almost gritstone pavement

properties.name: Grinah Stones
properties.desc: At the stones follow the path around the contour towards Bleaklow Stones. Fine gritstone outcrop, worth exploring

properties.name: Bleaklow Stones
properties.desc: Head almost due West on the faint rise and line of stakes to Bleaklow hill. Beautiful gritstone boulders

properties.name: Bleaklow Hill
properties.desc: The path here is hard to follow, there is a line of stakes bearing Southwest along the faint ridge. Navigation here can be tricky.

properties.name: Bleaklow
properties.desc: Follow the stakes West towards Bleaklow Head. Navigation is tricky here, Cloughs will lead you in circles!

properties.name: Bleaklow Head
properties.desc: Carry on to the Wain stones. Alternately take the left hand path that follows the stream

properties.name: Wain Stones
properties.desc: Turn left at the "kissing" Wain Stones, heading South on the Pennine way.

properties.name: Hern Stones
properties.desc:
Pass the gritstone boulders on you right 
 and bear right. Follow the clear path down toward the stream.

properties.name: Ford
properties.desc: Good water source

properties.name: Hern Clough
properties.desc: Turn left at Hern Clough along its Northern bank down stream. The path can be lost here.

properties.name: Ford
properties.desc: Bear left, take the higher ground if marshy

properties.name: The Swamp
properties.desc: Stay to the left and higher than you might be tempted

properties.name: Grains in the Water
properties.desc: A crossing and a bit of a scramble here

properties.name: River Alport
properties.desc: Follow the contour half way up the Eastern bank of the Alpot

properties.name: Miry Clough
properties.desc: You can skirt around or go directly across and scramble up the rocky clough opposite

properties.name: Glethering Clough
properties.desc: Track onto Alport moor top and head for the trig point

properties.name: Trig Point
properties.desc: Alport Moor

properties.name: Alport Castles
properties.desc: Take the 90 degree left out along the line of butts. Great view from the edge here.

properties.name: Hut
properties.desc: Take the left path at the shooting hut and carry on

properties.name: Fagney Plantation
properties.desc: Enter the plantation and carry on down hill

properties.name: Ditch Clough Plantation
properties.desc: Take the clear road right around the edge of River Westend towards Derwent

properties.name: Fairholmes
properties.desc: Caf, Toilets, Bins, Bus Stop, etc.

properties.name: Gate
properties.desc: Go through the gate into the woods

properties.name: Forest Track
properties.desc: Turn left on the forest track and follow it up hill

properties.name: Lockerbrook Coppice (1)
properties.desc: Turn hard left on the track heading up

properties.name: Lokerbrook Coppice (2)
properties.desc: The direct path up to the Outdoor Centre here can be very overgrown, head back and up

properties.name: Hagg Farm
properties.desc: Follow the winding track downhill passed Hagg Farm on your right

properties.name: Haggwater Bridge
properties.desc: Cross the bridge and carry on the clear trackway

properties.name: Crookstone Barn
properties.desc: Turn right to take the path up Crookstone Hill

properties.name: Crookstone Hill
properties.desc: Turn left onto the small path up Crookstone Hill

properties.name: Crookstone Knoll
properties.desc: Round the knoll and turn left to head West up the hill

properties.name: Blackden Edge
properties.desc: Follow the clear path West along the edge

properties.name: Blackden Brook

properties.desc: Gritstone edge

properties.name: Fair Brook
properties.desc: Cross the brook and turn hard right to keep to the edge

properties.name: Fairbrook Naze
properties.desc: Turn left to follow the edge as you reach the tip of Fairbrook Naze

properties.name: The Edge
properties.desc: Gritstone edge

properties.name: Ashop Head

properties.name: Trig Point
properties.desc: Kinder Low 633

properties.name: Edale Rocks

properties.name: Pym Chair
properties.desc: Gritstone outcrop

properties.desc: Gritstone Boulder field. Well worth exploring

properties.name: Crowden Tower
properties.desc: Gritstone outcrop

properties.name: Gridslow Knoll

properties.name: Upper Tor

properties.name: Nether Tor

properties.name: Scramble

properties.name: The Nab
properties.desc: Turn right and switch back downhill

properties.name: Steps
properties.desc: Go down the steps and cross the bridge

properties.name: Steps
properties.desc: Come up the steps and turn left on to the road

properties.name: Edale General Store
properties.desc:
Good shop, sells most things you might want

http://www.edalegeneralstore.com/

properties.name: Sheepfold

properties.name: Cairn

properties.name: Rushup Edge

properties.name: Lord's Seat

properties.desc: Pass Windy Knoll on your left

properties.name: Oxlow House

properties.name: Pub
properties.desc: The George

properties.name: Pub
properties.desc: The Castle

properties.name: Cross Street

Mam Tor 517.

properties.name: Viewpoint
